        "part_type": "Hadith",
        "path": "/books/kitab-al-ghayba-tusi:28:2",
        "source_url": "https://thaqalayn.net/hadith/27/1/28/2",
        "text": [
          "ه تعالى: ﴿وفِي السَّماءِ رِزْقُكُمْ وما تُوعَدُونَ﴾، قال: هو خروج المهدي عليه السلام."
        ],
        "translations": {
          "en.sayyid-athar-husain-s-h-rizvi": [
            "H 130 - The following verses of Quran prove that the rise of Imam Mahdi (a.s) is definite in this Ummah: It is narrated from Ibrahim bin Salma from Ahmad bin Malik Fuzari from Haider bin Muhammad Fuzari from Abbad bin Yaqub from Nasr bin Muzahim from Muhammad bin Marwan from Kulaini from Abi Salih from Ibn Abbas with regard to the verse: “And in the heaven is your sustenance and what you are threatened with…” (51:22-23) He said “It implies the rise of the Qaim of Aale Muhammad (a.s).”"
          ]
        }
      },
      {
        "index": 312,
        "local_index": 3,
        "narrator_chain": {
          "parts": [
            {
              "kind": "plain",
              "text": "s131- وبهذا الإسناد"
            },
            {
              "kind": "plain",
              "text": " عن ابن عباس في قوله: ﴿اعْلَمُوا أَنَّ"
            }
          ]
        },
        "part_type": "Hadith",
        "path": "/books/kitab-al-ghayba-tusi:28:3",
        "relations": {
          "Mentions": [
            "/books/quran:57:17"
          ]
        },
        "source_url": "https://thaqalayn.net/hadith/27/1/28/3",
        "text": [
          " اللَّهَ يُحْيِ الْأَرْضَ بَعْدَ مَوْتِها﴾: يعني يصلح الأرض بقائم آل محمد من بعد موتها. يعني من بعد جور أهل مملكتها ﴿قَدْ بَيَّنَّا لَكُمُ الْآياتِ﴾ بقائم آل محمد ﴿لَعَلَّكُمْ تَعْقِلُونَ﴾."
        ],
        "translations": {
          "en.sayyid-athar-husain-s-h-rizvi": [
            "H. 131 -From the same chain of narration from Ibn Abbas regarding the verse <a href=\"/books/quran:57#h17\">[57:17]</a>: «Know that Allah gives life to the earth after its death» : it means that Allah will restore the earth through the Qa'im from the family of Muhammad after its death, referring to the corruption of the people of its kingdom. «Indeed, We have clarified the verses for you» refers to the Qaim of the family of Muhammad, «so that you may understand.»"
          ]
        }
      },
